Stay toasty at these warming centers

Cold temperatures in Columbia have led officials to open overnight warming centers. Official centers offer beds and sometimes meals, while warming centers are available to the public during business hours at that location.

Sick of these colors? Make your own palette! To do so, create two squares, and put them next to each other but not touching, like this:
Select both squares, go to Object >> Blend >> Blend Options and select “Specified Steps” with 4 steps. Click “Okay.” Then, with both squares still selected, go back to Object >> Blend >> Make. Voila!
If you want to do the whole enchilada, make five adjacent squares and use the eyedropper to finalize your palette.
If you want a light color palette, make the square on the left white. If you want a darker color palette, make the square on the right black. Make the other square the color you like.
